{"id": "duc04-testb-24:9#27", "contents": "Robert F. Furchgott, Louis J. Ignarro, and Ferid Murad of the United States were awarded the Nobel Medicine Prize on Monday. The three researchers were recognized for their discoveries concerning nitric oxide as a signaling molecule in the cardiovascular system, as stated in the citation from the Karolinska Institute. Furchgott is a pharmacologist at the State University of New York in Brooklyn, while Ignarro is at the University of California-Los Angeles and Murad is at the University of Texas Medical School in Houston."}
